{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019ZMegTkqi3xAwUoRgLbyG5","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.direct;\n    17→\n    18→import jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n    19→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    20→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    21→\n    22→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeJDBC;\n    23→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    24→\n    25→// MIGRATION: Replaced @Resource UserTransaction with @Transactional annotation\n    26→@Dependent\n    27→public class AsyncOrder implements Runnable {\n    28→\n    29→  @Inject\n    30→  @TradeJDBC\n    31→  TradeServices tradeService;\n    32→      \n    33→  Integer orderID;\n    34→  boolean twoPhase;\n    35→  \n    36→  public void setProperties(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) {\n    37→    this.orderID = orderID;\n    38→    this.twoPhase =  twoPhase;\n    39→  }     \n    40→  \n    41→  @Override\n    42→  @Transactional\n    43→  public void run() {\n    44→        \n    45→        \n    46→    try {  \n    47→      tradeService.completeOrder(orderID, twoPhase);      \n    48→    } catch (Exception e) {\n    49→      \n    50→      try {\n    51→        throw new Exception(e);\n    52→      } catch (Exception e1) {\n    53→        e1.printStackTrace();\n    54→      }\n    55→    } \n    56→  }\n    57→}\n    58→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"c0d70733-0fca-4894-966b-ac4a7ed83be4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XGKtMQKiVvEv7njWmzHV8b","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.direct;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.concurrent.CompletableFuture;\n    19→import java.util.concurrent.Future;\n    20→\n    21→import jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;\n    22→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    23→\n    24→import io.quarkus.virtual.threads.VirtualThreads;\n    25→import java.util.concurrent.ExecutorService;\n    26→\n    27→// MIGRATION: ManagedExecutorService -> Quarkus ExecutorService with virtual threads\n    28→@RequestScoped\n    29→public class AsyncOrderSubmitter {\n    30→  \n    31→  @Inject\n    32→  @VirtualThreads\n    33→  ExecutorService executorService;\n    34→\n    35→  @Inject\n    36→  private AsyncOrder asyncOrder;\n    37→  \n    38→  \n    39→  public Future<?> submitOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) {\n    40→    asyncOrder.setProperties(orderID,twoPhase);\n    41→    return CompletableFuture.runAsync(asyncOrder, executorService);\n    42→  }\n    43→}\n    44→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"bb954726-717c-4ddb-8ed7-2b1f129a5ba4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BpjmHcyQTUmGD9fDKLhyRy","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.ejb3;\n    17→\n    18→// MIGRATION: javax.* -> jakarta.*\n    19→import jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n    20→import jakarta.enterprise.inject.Any;\n    21→import jakarta.enterprise.inject.Instance;\n    22→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    23→\n    24→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    25→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    26→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeRunTimeModeLiteral;\n    27→\n    28→\n    29→@Dependent\n    30→public class AsyncScheduledOrder implements Runnable {\n    31→\n    32→  TradeServices tradeService;\n    33→\n    34→  Integer orderID;\n    35→  boolean twoPhase;\n    36→\n    37→  @Inject \n    38→  public AsyncScheduledOrder(@Any Instance<TradeServices> services) {\n    39→    tradeService = services.select(new TradeRunTimeModeLiteral(TradeConfig.getRunTimeModeNames()[TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode()])).get();\n    40→  }\n    41→\n    42→  public void setProperties(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) {\n    43→    this.orderID = orderID;\n    44→    this.twoPhase =  twoPhase;\n    45→  }     \n    46→\n    47→  @Override\n    48→  public void run() {\n    49→\n    50→\n    51→    try {  \n    52→      tradeService.completeOrder(orderID, twoPhase);      \n    53→\n    54→    } catch (Exception e) {\n    55→\n    56→      e.printStackTrace();\n    57→    }\n    58→  }\n    59→}\n    60→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"74d52e2e-8287-403a-8f1a-c28cd4ef59e8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Jx8JfNHG4dn52o1T67Ners","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.ejb3;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.concurrent.CompletableFuture;\n    19→import java.util.concurrent.Future;\n    20→import java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;\n    21→\n    22→// MIGRATION: javax.* -> jakarta.*\n    23→// MIGRATION: ManagedScheduledExecutorService -> Quarkus ExecutorService\n    24→import jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;\n    25→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    26→\n    27→import io.quarkus.virtual.threads.VirtualThreads;\n    28→import java.util.concurrent.ExecutorService;\n    29→\n    30→@RequestScoped\n    31→public class AsyncScheduledOrderSubmitter {\n    32→  \n    33→  @Inject\n    34→  @VirtualThreads\n    35→  ExecutorService executorService;\n    36→\n    37→  @Inject\n    38→  private AsyncScheduledOrder asyncOrder;\n    39→  \n    40→  \n    41→  public Future<?> submitOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) {\n    42→    asyncOrder.setProperties(orderID,twoPhase);\n    43→    // MIGRATION: Use CompletableFuture with delay instead of scheduled executor\n    44→    return CompletableFuture.runAsync(() -> {\n    45→      try {\n    46→        TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS.sleep(500);\n    47→        asyncOrder.run();\n    48→      } catch (InterruptedException e) {\n    49→        Thread.currentThread().interrupt();\n    50→      }\n    51→    }, executorService);\n    52→  }\n    53→}\n    54→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"6ac5e6a1-e97c-4e74-99a6-762607ad4022"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TdjxuDTtyRcnFb5eF76ArH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.session2direct;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→import java.util.Collection;\n    20→import java.util.concurrent.Future;\n    21→\n    22→// MIGRATION: javax.* -> jakarta.*\n    23→// MIGRATION: @Stateless EJB -> @ApplicationScoped CDI\n    24→// MIGRATION: @TransactionAttribute -> @Transactional\n    25→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    26→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    27→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    28→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    29→\n    30→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.RuntimeMode;\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;\n    32→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeJDBC;\n    33→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeSession2Direct;\n    35→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.MarketSummaryDataBean;\n    36→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n    37→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\n    38→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\n    39→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.OrderDataBean;\n    40→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    41→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.ejb3.AsyncScheduledOrderSubmitter;\n    42→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    43→\n    44→// MIGRATION: @Stateless -> @ApplicationScoped\n    45→// MIGRATION: @TransactionAttribute(REQUIRED) -> @Transactional\n    46→// DirectSLSBBean delegates to TradeDirect for the \"Session to Direct\" mode\n    47→// The @TradeSession2Direct qualifier ensures it's only injected when explicitly requested\n    48→@ApplicationScoped\n    49→@TradeSession2Direct\n    50→@RuntimeMode(\"Session to Direct\")\n    51→@Trace\n    52→@Transactional\n    53→public class DirectSLSBBean implements TradeServices {\n    54→\n    55→  @Inject\n    56→  @TradeJDBC\n    57→  TradeServices tradeDirect;\n    58→  \n    59→  @Inject \n    60→  AsyncScheduledOrderSubmitter asyncEJBOrderSubmitter; \n    61→\n    62→  @Override\n    63→  public int getImpl() {\n    64→    return TradeConfig.SESSION_TO_DIRECT;\n    65→  }\n    66→\n    67→  @Override\n    68→  public MarketSummaryDataBean getMarketSummary() throws Exception {\n    69→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n    70→    return tradeDirect.getMarketSummary();\n    71→  }\n    72→\n    73→  @Override\n    74→  public OrderDataBean createOrder(AccountDataBean account, QuoteDataBean quote, HoldingDataBean holding,\n    75→      String orderType, double quantity) throws Exception {\n    76→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n    77→    return tradeDirect.createOrder(account, quote, holding, orderType, quantity);\n    78→  }\n    79→\n    80→  @Override\n    81→  @NotNull\n    82→  public OrderDataBean buy(String userID, String symbol, double quantity, int orderProcessingMode) throws Exception {\n    83→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n    84→     OrderDataBean orderdata = tradeDirect.buy(userID, symbol, quantity, orderProcessingMode);\n    85→    \n    86→    if (orderProcessingMode == TradeConfig.ASYNCH) {\n    87→      this.completeOrderAsync(orderdata.getOrderID(), false);\n    88→    }\n    89→    \n    90→    return orderdata; \n    91→  }\n    92→\n    93→  @Override\n    94→  @NotNull\n    95→  public OrderDataBean sell(String userID, Integer holdingID, int orderProcessingMode) throws Exception {\n    96→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n    97→    OrderDataBean orderdata =  tradeDirect.sell(userID, holdingID, orderProcessingMode);\n    98→    \n    99→    if (orderProcessingMode == TradeConfig.ASYNCH) {\n   100→      this.completeOrderAsync(orderdata.getOrderID(), false);\n   101→    }\n   102→    return orderdata;\n   103→    \n   104→  }\n   105→\n   106→  @Override\n   107→  public void queueOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception {\n   108→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   109→    tradeDirect.queueOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n   110→\n   111→  }\n   112→\n   113→  @Override\n   114→  public OrderDataBean completeOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception {\n   115→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   116→    return tradeDirect.completeOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n   117→  }\n   118→\n   119→  @Override\n   120→  public Future<OrderDataBean> completeOrderAsync(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception {\n   121→    asyncEJBOrderSubmitter.submitOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n   122→    return null;\n   123→  }\n   124→\n   125→  @Override\n   126→  public void cancelOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception {\n   127→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   128→    tradeDirect.cancelOrder(orderID, twoPhase);\n   129→\n   130→  }\n   131→\n   132→  @Override\n   133→  public void orderCompleted(String userID, Integer orderID) throws Exception {\n   134→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   135→    tradeDirect.orderCompleted(userID, orderID);\n   136→\n   137→  }\n   138→\n   139→  @Override\n   140→  public Collection<?> getOrders(String userID) throws Exception {\n   141→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   142→    return tradeDirect.getOrders(userID);\n   143→  }\n   144→\n   145→  @Override\n   146→  public Collection<?> getClosedOrders(String userID) throws Exception {\n   147→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   148→    return tradeDirect.getClosedOrders(userID);\n   149→  }\n   150→\n   151→  @Override\n   152→  public QuoteDataBean createQuote(String symbol, String companyName, BigDecimal price) throws Exception {\n   153→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   154→    return tradeDirect.createQuote(symbol, companyName, price);\n   155→  }\n   156→\n   157→  @Override\n   158→  public QuoteDataBean getQuote(String symbol) throws Exception {\n   159→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   160→    return tradeDirect.getQuote(symbol); \n   161→  }\n   162→\n   163→  @Override\n   164→  public Collection<?> getAllQuotes() throws Exception {\n   165→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   166→    return tradeDirect.getAllQuotes();\n   167→  }\n   168→\n   169→  @Override\n   170→  public QuoteDataBean updateQuotePriceVolume(String symbol, BigDecimal newPrice, double sharesTraded)\n   171→      throws Exception {\n   172→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   173→    return tradeDirect.updateQuotePriceVolume(symbol, newPrice, sharesTraded);\n   174→  }\n   175→\n   176→  @Override\n   177→  public Collection<HoldingDataBean> getHoldings(String userID) throws Exception {\n   178→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   179→    return tradeDirect.getHoldings(userID);\n   180→  }\n   181→\n   182→  @Override\n   183→  public HoldingDataBean getHolding(Integer holdingID) throws Exception {\n   184→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   185→    return tradeDirect.getHolding(holdingID);\n   186→  }\n   187→\n   188→  @Override\n   189→  public AccountDataBean getAccountData(String userID) throws Exception {\n   190→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   191→    return tradeDirect.getAccountData(userID);\n   192→  }\n   193→\n   194→  @Override\n   195→  public AccountProfileDataBean getAccountProfileData(String userID) throws Exception {\n   196→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   197→    return tradeDirect.getAccountProfileData(userID);\n   198→  }\n   199→\n   200→  @Override\n   201→  public AccountProfileDataBean updateAccountProfile(AccountProfileDataBean profileData) throws Exception {\n   202→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   203→    return tradeDirect.updateAccountProfile(profileData);\n   204→  }\n   205→\n   206→  @Override\n   207→  public AccountDataBean login(String userID, String password) throws Exception {\n   208→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   209→    return tradeDirect.login(userID, password);\n   210→  }\n   211→\n   212→  @Override\n   213→  public void logout(String userID) throws Exception {\n   214→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   215→    tradeDirect.logout(userID);\n   216→  }\n   217→\n   218→  @Override\n   219→  public AccountDataBean register(String userID, String password, String fullname, String address, String email,\n   220→      String creditcard, BigDecimal openBalance) throws Exception {\n   221→    tradeDirect.setInSession(true);\n   222→    return tradeDirect.register(userID, password, fullname, address, email, creditcard, openBalance);\n   223→  }\n   224→\n   225→  @Override\n   226→  public QuoteDataBean pingTwoPhase(String symbol) throws Exception {\n   227→    throw new UnsupportedOperationException();\n   228→  }\n   229→\n   230→  @Override\n   231→  public double investmentReturn(double rnd1, double rnd2) throws Exception {\n   232→    throw new UnsupportedOperationException();\n   233→  }\n   234→\n   235→\n   236→  @Override\n   237→  public void setInSession(boolean inSession) {\n   238→    throw new UnsupportedOperationException(\"DirectSLSBBean::setInGlobalTxn not supported\");\n   239→  }\n   240→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"6bf4d816-4f96-4c9e-8aac-b2b0a8a206e4"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_012xQN7ZDhiP5ND6wK7rGmf5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me update my todo and begin the migration. This is a Quarkus application that needs to become a standard Jakarta EE application. The key Quarkus-specific dependencies and patterns I need to replace are:\n\n1. **Quarkus-specific imports**: `io.quarkus.*`, `io.smallrye.*`, `org.eclipse.microprofile.*`\n2. **Quarkus annotations**: `@Scheduled`, `StartupEvent`, `@VirtualThreads`, `@Channel`, `@Incoming`, `@Broadcast`\n3. **Quarkus-specific APIs**: `QuarkusTransaction`, `AgroalDataSource`\n4. **Reactive Messaging** -> JMS\n5. **Config**: `@ConfigProperty` -> standard approach\n6. **Build**: Quarkus Maven plugin -> standard WAR deployment on an app server like Open Liberty or WildFly\n\nLet me plan and execute:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":30695,"cache_read_input_tokens":80507,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":30695,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":825},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"79b1cdbd-27d4-4eca-ac61-08716f8993c2"}
