{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014dRW8TRwfH5NNWLDAN3PYJ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have successfully created all 5 configuration files for your Jakarta EE application migration from Quarkus to Open Liberty. Here's a summary of what was created:\n\n## Created Configuration Files\n\n### 1. Open Liberty Server Configuration\n**File:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/liberty/config/server.xml`\n- Configures Jakarta EE 10.0 features with MicroProfile Config 3.1\n- Sets up HTTP endpoints on ports 8080 (HTTP) and 8443 (HTTPS)\n- Configures H2 in-memory database with JNDI name `jdbc/TradeDataSource`\n- Sets up JMS messaging with queues and topics for TradeBroker and TradeStreamer MDBs\n- Configures the daytrader web application with root context\n\n### 2. JPA Persistence Configuration\n**File:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/resources/META-INF/persistence.xml`\n- Defines the \"daytrader\" persistence unit using JTA transactions\n- References the TradeDataSource JNDI name\n- Lists all entity classes (AccountDataBean, AccountProfileDataBean, HoldingDataBean, OrderDataBean, QuoteDataBean)\n- Configures schema generation to drop-and-create on startup with H2 dialect\n\n### 3. Web Deployment Descriptor\n**File:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/web.xml`\n- Jakarta EE 6.0 web application descriptor\n- Minimal configuration for servlet 6.0 specification\n\n### 4. CDI Beans Descriptor\n**File:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/beans.xml`\n- Jakarta CDI 4.0 configuration\n- Enables full CDI with bean-discovery-mode=\"all\"\n\n### 5. MicroProfile Config Properties\n**File:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/resources/META-INF/microprofile-config.properties`\n- Application-specific configuration for DayTrader\n- Sets runtime mode to EJB3, synchronous order processing\n- Configures maximum users (50) and quotes (100)\n- Enables database population on startup\n\nAll files have been created successfully and are ready for your Open Liberty deployment."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"8178b131-4177-4b63-881b-56bf06996b67"}
