{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_012puHxbeNewy25UZaZkLyBz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01Q13m9MLXCGw9ZCUaNx9tTW","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/ejb3/MarketSummarySingleton.java"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":18674,"cache_read_input_tokens":23572,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":18674,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":260},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YNn66n2h4yBgnSbLqJ6KDJ","session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"589c7692-571d-4516-ac9b-31f9746f9173"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01AsdHbTAKgexPyTZRwhNWym","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015, 2024.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.startup;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→\n    20→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    21→import jakarta.enterprise.event.Observes;\n    22→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    23→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n    24→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    25→\n    26→import org.eclipse.microprofile.config.inject.ConfigProperty;\n    27→\n    28→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n    29→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\n    30→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    32→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    33→\n    34→import io.quarkus.runtime.StartupEvent;\n    35→\n    36→/**\n    37→ * Populates the database with initial data on application startup.\n    38→ * This replaces the manual \"Populate Database\" action from the Jakarta EE version.\n    39→ */\n    40→@ApplicationScoped\n    41→public class DatabasePopulator {\n    42→\n    43→    @Inject\n    44→    EntityManager em;\n    45→\n    46→    @ConfigProperty(name = \"trade.db.populate.on.startup\", defaultValue = \"true\")\n    47→    boolean populateOnStartup;\n    48→\n    49→    @ConfigProperty(name = \"trade.max.users\", defaultValue = \"50\")\n    50→    int maxUsers;\n    51→\n    52→    @ConfigProperty(name = \"trade.max.quotes\", defaultValue = \"100\")\n    53→    int maxQuotes;\n    54→\n    55→    @Transactional\n    56→    void onStart(@Observes StartupEvent ev) {\n    57→        if (!populateOnStartup) {\n    58→            Log.log(\"Database population disabled via configuration\");\n    59→            return;\n    60→        }\n    61→\n    62→        // Check if database already has data (using native SQL since entity names are lowercase)\n    63→        Number quoteCount = (Number) em.createNativeQuery(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM quoteejb\").getSingleResult();\n    64→        if (quoteCount.longValue() > 0) {\n    65→            Log.log(\"Database already populated with \" + quoteCount + \" quotes. Skipping population.\");\n    66→            return;\n    67→        }\n    68→\n    69→        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Populating DayTrader Database on startup...\");\n    70→        \n    71→        try {\n    72→            populateQuotes();\n    73→            populateUsers();\n    74→            Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Database population complete!\");\n    75→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    76→            Log.error(e, \"TradeBuildDB: Error populating database\");\n    77→        }\n    78→    }\n    79→\n    80→    private void populateQuotes() {\n    81→        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Creating \" + maxQuotes + \" Quotes...\");\n    82→        \n    83→        for (int i = 0; i < maxQuotes; i++) {\n    84→            String symbol = \"s:\" + i;\n    85→            String companyName = \"S\" + i + \" Incorporated\";\n    86→            BigDecimal price = new BigDecimal(TradeConfig.rndPrice());\n    87→            \n    88→            QuoteDataBean quote = new QuoteDataBean();\n    89→            quote.setSymbol(symbol);\n    90→            quote.setCompanyName(companyName);\n    91→            quote.setPrice(price);\n    92→            quote.setOpen(price);\n    93→            quote.setLow(price);\n    94→            quote.setHigh(price);\n    95→            quote.setChange(0.0);\n    96→            quote.setVolume(0.0);\n    97→            \n    98→            em.persist(quote);\n    99→            \n   100→            if (i % 10 == 0) {\n   101→                Log.log(\"Created quote: \" + symbol);\n   102→            }\n   103→        }\n   104→        em.flush();\n   105→    }\n   106→\n   107→    private void populateUsers() {\n   108→        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Registering \" + maxUsers + \" Users...\");\n   109→        \n   110→        for (int i = 0; i < maxUsers; i++) {\n   111→            String userID = \"uid:\" + i;\n   112→            String fullname = TradeConfig.rndFullName();\n   113→            String email = TradeConfig.rndEmail(userID);\n   114→            String address = TradeConfig.rndAddress();\n   115→            String creditcard = TradeConfig.rndCreditCard();\n   116→            BigDecimal initialBalance = new BigDecimal((double) (TradeConfig.rndInt(100000)) + 200000);\n   117→            \n   118→            if (i == 0) {\n   119→                initialBalance = new BigDecimal(1000000); // uid:0 starts with a cool million.\n   120→            }\n   121→            \n   122→            // Create profile\n   123→            AccountProfileDataBean profile = new AccountProfileDataBean();\n   124→            profile.setUserID(userID);\n   125→            profile.setPassword(\"xxx\");\n   126→            profile.setFullName(fullname);\n   127→            profile.setAddress(address);\n   128→            profile.setEmail(email);\n   129→            profile.setCreditCard(creditcard);\n   130→            em.persist(profile);\n   131→            \n   132→            // Create account\n   133→            AccountDataBean account = new AccountDataBean();\n   134→            account.setProfile(profile);\n   135→            account.setCreationDate(new java.sql.Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n   136→            account.setLastLogin(new java.sql.Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n   137→            account.setBalance(initialBalance);\n   138→            account.setOpenBalance(initialBalance);\n   139→            account.setLoginCount(0);\n   140→            account.setLogoutCount(0);\n   141→            em.persist(account);\n   142→            \n   143→            if (i % 10 == 0) {\n   144→                Log.log(\"Registered user: \" + userID + \" with balance: \" + initialBalance);\n   145→            }\n   146→        }\n   147→        em.flush();\n   148→    }\n   149→}\n   150→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YNn66n2h4yBgnSbLqJ6KDJ","session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"82960ab3-26b2-49be-aeec-b333af6cc811"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Q13m9MLXCGw9ZCUaNx9tTW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.ejb3;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    20→import java.util.List;\n    21→\n    22→// MIGRATION: javax.* -> jakarta.*\n    23→// MIGRATION: @Singleton EJB -> @ApplicationScoped CDI\n    24→// MIGRATION: @Schedule -> @Scheduled (Quarkus)\n    25→// MIGRATION: @Lock -> synchronized methods\n    26→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    27→import jakarta.enterprise.event.Event;\n    28→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    29→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n    30→import jakarta.persistence.TypedQuery;\n    31→import jakarta.persistence.criteria.CriteriaBuilder;\n    32→import jakarta.persistence.criteria.CriteriaQuery;\n    33→import jakarta.persistence.criteria.Root;\n    34→\n    35→import io.quarkus.scheduler.Scheduled;\n    36→\n    37→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.MarketSummaryDataBean;\n    38→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    39→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.MarketSummaryUpdate;\n    40→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.FinancialUtils;\n    41→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    42→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    43→\n    44→// MIGRATION: @Singleton EJB -> @ApplicationScoped CDI bean\n    45→@ApplicationScoped\n    46→public class MarketSummarySingleton {\n    47→\n    48→  private volatile MarketSummaryDataBean marketSummaryDataBean;\n    49→\n    50→  @Inject\n    51→  EntityManager entityManager;\n    52→  \n    53→  @Inject\n    54→  @MarketSummaryUpdate\n    55→  Event<String> mkSummaryUpdateEvent;\n    56→  \n    57→  // MIGRATION: ManagedExecutorService removed, use simple fireAsync()\n    58→  \n    59→\n    60→  /* Update Market Summary every 20 seconds */\n    61→  // MIGRATION: @Schedule -> @Scheduled (Quarkus)\n    62→  @Scheduled(every = \"20s\")\n    63→  void updateMarketSummary() { \n    64→\n    65→\n    66→    Log.trace(\"MarketSummarySingleton:updateMarketSummary -- updating market summary\");\n    67→\n    68→\n    69→    if (TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode() != TradeConfig.EJB3)\n    70→    {\n    71→      Log.trace(\"MarketSummarySingleton:updateMarketSummary -- Not EJB3 Mode, so not updating periodically\");\n    72→      return; // Only do the periodic update if in EJB3 Mode\n    73→    }\n    74→\n    75→    computeMarketSummary();\n    76→    // MIGRATION: ManagedExecutorService removed, use simple fireAsync()\n    77→    mkSummaryUpdateEvent.fireAsync(\"MarketSummaryUpdate\");\n    78→  }\n    79→\n    80→  // MIGRATION: @Lock(READ) -> synchronized getter (volatile field provides visibility)\n    81→  public synchronized MarketSummaryDataBean getMarketSummaryDataBean() { \n    82→    if (marketSummaryDataBean == null){\n    83→      // Compute market summary on first access regardless of mode\n    84→      computeMarketSummary();\n    85→    }\n    86→\n    87→    return marketSummaryDataBean;\n    88→  }\n    89→\n    90→  // Internal method to compute market summary (called on-demand or by scheduler)\n    91→  private void computeMarketSummary() {\n    92→    List<QuoteDataBean> quotes;\n    93→\n    94→    try {        \n    95→      // Find Trade Stock Index Quotes (Top 100 quotes) ordered by their change in value\n    96→      CriteriaBuilder criteriaBuilder = entityManager.getCriteriaBuilder();\n    97→      CriteriaQuery<QuoteDataBean> criteriaQuery = criteriaBuilder.createQuery(QuoteDataBean.class);\n    98→      Root<QuoteDataBean> quoteRoot = criteriaQuery.from(QuoteDataBean.class);\n    99→      criteriaQuery.orderBy(criteriaBuilder.desc(quoteRoot.get(\"change1\")));\n   100→      criteriaQuery.select(quoteRoot);\n   101→      TypedQuery<QuoteDataBean> q = entityManager.createQuery(criteriaQuery);\n   102→      quotes = q.getResultList();\n   103→    } catch (Exception e) {\n   104→      Log.debug(\"Warning: The database has not been configured. If this is the first time the application has been started, please create and populate the database tables. Then restart the server.\");\n   105→      return;\n   106→    }\t\n   107→\n   108→    /* TODO: Make this cleaner? */\n   109→    QuoteDataBean[] quoteArray = quotes.toArray(new QuoteDataBean[quotes.size()]);\n   110→    ArrayList<QuoteDataBean> topGainers = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>(5);\n   111→    ArrayList<QuoteDataBean> topLosers = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>(5);\n   112→    BigDecimal TSIA = FinancialUtils.ZERO;\n   113→    BigDecimal openTSIA = FinancialUtils.ZERO;\n   114→    double totalVolume = 0.0;\n   115→\n   116→    if (quoteArray.length > 5) {\n   117→      for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {\n   118→        topGainers.add(quoteArray[i]);\n   119→      }\n   120→      for (int i = quoteArray.length - 1; i >= quoteArray.length - 5; i--) {\n   121→        topLosers.add(quoteArray[i]);\n   122→      }\n   123→\n   124→      for (QuoteDataBean quote : quoteArray) {\n   125→        BigDecimal price = quote.getPrice();\n   126→        BigDecimal open = quote.getOpen();\n   127→        double volume = quote.getVolume();\n   128→        TSIA = TSIA.add(price);\n   129→        openTSIA = openTSIA.add(open);\n   130→        totalVolume += volume;\n   131→      }\n   132→      TSIA = TSIA.divide(new BigDecimal(quoteArray.length), FinancialUtils.ROUND);\n   133→      openTSIA = openTSIA.divide(new BigDecimal(quoteArray.length), FinancialUtils.ROUND);\n   134→    }\n   135→\n   136→    setMarketSummaryDataBean(new MarketSummaryDataBean(TSIA, openTSIA, totalVolume, topGainers, topLosers));\n   137→  }\n   138→\n   139→  // MIGRATION: @Lock(WRITE) -> synchronized setter\n   140→  public synchronized void setMarketSummaryDataBean(MarketSummaryDataBean marketSummaryDataBean) {\n   141→    this.marketSummaryDataBean = marketSummaryDataBean;\n   142→  }\n   143→\n   144→}\n   145→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YNn66n2h4yBgnSbLqJ6KDJ","session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"9cf16b95-afc0-4281-8d11-029e87db7cd4"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_01H2nTLAjacvL8p1MfqjXETJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_013RwNxHsQkgCXZdpG8f389S","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/startup/DatabasePopulator.java","content":"/**\n * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015, 2024.\n *\n * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n *\n * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n *\n * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n * limitations under the License.\n */\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.startup;\n\nimport java.math.BigDecimal;\n\nimport jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\nimport jakarta.ejb.Singleton;\nimport jakarta.ejb.Startup;\nimport jakarta.ejb.TransactionAttribute;\nimport jakarta.ejb.TransactionAttributeType;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\nimport jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.config.inject.ConfigProperty;\n\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n\n/**\n * Populates the database with initial data on application startup.\n */\n@Singleton\n@Startup\npublic class DatabasePopulator {\n\n    @PersistenceContext(unitName = \"daytrader\")\n    EntityManager em;\n\n    @Inject\n    @ConfigProperty(name = \"trade.db.populate.on.startup\", defaultValue = \"true\")\n    boolean populateOnStartup;\n\n    @Inject\n    @ConfigProperty(name = \"trade.max.users\", defaultValue = \"50\")\n    int maxUsers;\n\n    @Inject\n    @ConfigProperty(name = \"trade.max.quotes\", defaultValue = \"100\")\n    int maxQuotes;\n\n    @PostConstruct\n    @TransactionAttribute(TransactionAttributeType.REQUIRED)\n    void onStart() {\n        if (!populateOnStartup) {\n            Log.log(\"Database population disabled via configuration\");\n            return;\n        }\n\n        try {\n            Number quoteCount = (Number) em.createNativeQuery(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM quoteejb\").getSingleResult();\n            if (quoteCount.longValue() > 0) {\n                Log.log(\"Database already populated with \" + quoteCount + \" quotes. Skipping population.\");\n                return;\n            }\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            // Table may not exist yet, proceed with population\n            Log.log(\"Database tables may not exist yet, proceeding with population...\");\n        }\n\n        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Populating DayTrader Database on startup...\");\n\n        try {\n            populateQuotes();\n            populateUsers();\n            Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Database population complete!\");\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            Log.error(e, \"TradeBuildDB: Error populating database\");\n        }\n    }\n\n    private void populateQuotes() {\n        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Creating \" + maxQuotes + \" Quotes...\");\n\n        for (int i = 0; i < maxQuotes; i++) {\n            String symbol = \"s:\" + i;\n            String companyName = \"S\" + i + \" Incorporated\";\n            BigDecimal price = new BigDecimal(TradeConfig.rndPrice());\n\n            QuoteDataBean quote = new QuoteDataBean();\n            quote.setSymbol(symbol);\n            quote.setCompanyName(companyName);\n            quote.setPrice(price);\n            quote.setOpen(price);\n            quote.setLow(price);\n            quote.setHigh(price);\n            quote.setChange(0.0);\n            quote.setVolume(0.0);\n\n            em.persist(quote);\n\n            if (i % 10 == 0) {\n                Log.log(\"Created quote: \" + symbol);\n            }\n        }\n        em.flush();\n    }\n\n    private void populateUsers() {\n        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Registering \" + maxUsers + \" Users...\");\n\n        for (int i = 0; i < maxUsers; i++) {\n            String userID = \"uid:\" + i;\n            String fullname = TradeConfig.rndFullName();\n            String email = TradeConfig.rndEmail(userID);\n            String address = TradeConfig.rndAddress();\n            String creditcard = TradeConfig.rndCreditCard();\n            BigDecimal initialBalance = new BigDecimal((double) (TradeConfig.rndInt(100000)) + 200000);\n\n            if (i == 0) {\n                initialBalance = new BigDecimal(1000000);\n            }\n\n            AccountProfileDataBean profile = new AccountProfileDataBean();\n            profile.setUserID(userID);\n            profile.setPassword(\"xxx\");\n            profile.setFullName(fullname);\n            profile.setAddress(address);\n            profile.setEmail(email);\n            profile.setCreditCard(creditcard);\n            em.persist(profile);\n\n            AccountDataBean account = new AccountDataBean();\n            account.setProfile(profile);\n            account.setCreationDate(new java.sql.Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n            account.setLastLogin(new java.sql.Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n            account.setBalance(initialBalance);\n            account.setOpenBalance(initialBalance);\n            account.setLoginCount(0);\n            account.setLogoutCount(0);\n            em.persist(account);\n\n            if (i % 10 == 0) {\n                Log.log(\"Registered user: \" + userID + \" with balance: \" + initialBalance);\n            }\n        }\n        em.flush();\n    }\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4725,"cache_read_input_tokens":42246,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4725,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3428},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YNn66n2h4yBgnSbLqJ6KDJ","session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"f89f3888-3809-4c3f-b828-556c370fb59c"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_01H2nTLAjacvL8p1MfqjXETJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01WPsRF7cW3JuFk4XkHfp3Zw","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/ejb3/MarketSummarySingleton.java","content":"/**\n * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n *\n * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n *\n * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n *\n * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n * limitations under the License.\n */\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.ejb3;\n\nimport java.math.BigDecimal;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.List;\n\nimport jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\nimport jakarta.ejb.Lock;\nimport jakarta.ejb.LockType;\nimport jakarta.ejb.Schedule;\nimport jakarta.ejb.Singleton;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.event.Event;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\nimport jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\nimport jakarta.persistence.TypedQuery;\nimport jakarta.persistence.criteria.CriteriaBuilder;\nimport jakarta.persistence.criteria.CriteriaQuery;\nimport jakarta.persistence.criteria.Root;\n\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.MarketSummaryDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.MarketSummaryUpdate;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.FinancialUtils;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n\n@Singleton\npublic class MarketSummarySingleton {\n\n    private volatile MarketSummaryDataBean marketSummaryDataBean;\n\n    @PersistenceContext(unitName = \"daytrader\")\n    EntityManager entityManager;\n\n    @Inject\n    @MarketSummaryUpdate\n    Event<String> mkSummaryUpdateEvent;\n\n    @PostConstruct\n    void init() {\n        Log.trace(\"MarketSummarySingleton:init()\");\n    }\n\n    @Schedule(second = \"*/20\", minute = \"*\", hour = \"*\", persistent = false)\n    void updateMarketSummary() {\n        Log.trace(\"MarketSummarySingleton:updateMarketSummary -- updating market summary\");\n\n        if (TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode() != TradeConfig.EJB3) {\n            Log.trace(\"MarketSummarySingleton:updateMarketSummary -- Not EJB3 Mode, so not updating periodically\");\n            return;\n        }\n\n        computeMarketSummary();\n        try {\n            mkSummaryUpdateEvent.fireAsync(\"MarketSummaryUpdate\");\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            Log.trace(\"MarketSummarySingleton:updateMarketSummary -- async event fire failed (non-critical): \" + e.getMessage());\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Lock(LockType.READ)\n    public MarketSummaryDataBean getMarketSummaryDataBean() {\n        if (marketSummaryDataBean == null) {\n            computeMarketSummary();\n        }\n        return marketSummaryDataBean;\n    }\n\n    private void computeMarketSummary() {\n        List<QuoteDataBean> quotes;\n\n        try {\n            CriteriaBuilder criteriaBuilder = entityManager.getCriteriaBuilder();\n            CriteriaQuery<QuoteDataBean> criteriaQuery = criteriaBuilder.createQuery(QuoteDataBean.class);\n            Root<QuoteDataBean> quoteRoot = criteriaQuery.from(QuoteDataBean.class);\n            criteriaQuery.orderBy(criteriaBuilder.desc(quoteRoot.get(\"change1\")));\n            criteriaQuery.select(quoteRoot);\n            TypedQuery<QuoteDataBean> q = entityManager.createQuery(criteriaQuery);\n            quotes = q.getResultList();\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            Log.debug(\"Warning: The database has not been configured. If this is the first time the application has been started, please create and populate the database tables. Then restart the server.\");\n            return;\n        }\n\n        QuoteDataBean[] quoteArray = quotes.toArray(new QuoteDataBean[quotes.size()]);\n        ArrayList<QuoteDataBean> topGainers = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>(5);\n        ArrayList<QuoteDataBean> topLosers = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>(5);\n        BigDecimal TSIA = FinancialUtils.ZERO;\n        BigDecimal openTSIA = FinancialUtils.ZERO;\n        double totalVolume = 0.0;\n\n        if (quoteArray.length > 5) {\n            for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {\n                topGainers.add(quoteArray[i]);\n            }\n            for (int i = quoteArray.length - 1; i >= quoteArray.length - 5; i--) {\n                topLosers.add(quoteArray[i]);\n            }\n\n            for (QuoteDataBean quote : quoteArray) {\n                BigDecimal price = quote.getPrice();\n                BigDecimal open = quote.getOpen();\n                double volume = quote.getVolume();\n                TSIA = TSIA.add(price);\n                openTSIA = openTSIA.add(open);\n                totalVolume += volume;\n            }\n            TSIA = TSIA.divide(new BigDecimal(quoteArray.length), FinancialUtils.ROUND);\n            openTSIA = openTSIA.divide(new BigDecimal(quoteArray.length), FinancialUtils.ROUND);\n        }\n\n        setMarketSummaryDataBean(new MarketSummaryDataBean(TSIA, openTSIA, totalVolume, topGainers, topLosers));\n    }\n\n    @Lock(LockType.WRITE)\n    public void setMarketSummaryDataBean(MarketSummaryDataBean marketSummaryDataBean) {\n        this.marketSummaryDataBean = marketSummaryDataBean;\n    }\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4725,"cache_read_input_tokens":42246,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4725,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3428},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YNn66n2h4yBgnSbLqJ6KDJ","session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"1f6e7f71-7ec4-4dde-9de7-ca81f7402b6e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013RwNxHsQkgCXZdpG8f389S","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/startup/DatabasePopulator.java has been updated. Here's the result of running `cat -n` on a snippet of the edited file:\n     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015, 2024.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.startup;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→\n    20→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n    21→import jakarta.ejb.Singleton;\n    22→import jakarta.ejb.Startup;\n    23→import jakarta.ejb.TransactionAttribute;\n    24→import jakarta.ejb.TransactionAttributeType;\n    25→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    26→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n    27→import jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n    28→\n    29→import org.eclipse.microprofile.config.inject.ConfigProperty;\n    30→\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n    32→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\n    33→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    35→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    36→\n    37→/**\n    38→ * Populates the database with initial data on application startup.\n    39→ */\n    40→@Singleton\n    41→@Startup\n    42→public class DatabasePopulator {\n    43→\n    44→    @PersistenceContext(unitName = \"daytrader\")\n    45→    EntityManager em;\n    46→\n    47→    @Inject\n    48→    @ConfigProperty(name = \"trade.db.populate.on.startup\", defaultValue = \"true\")\n    49→    boolean populateOnStartup;\n    50→\n    51→    @Inject\n    52→    @ConfigProperty(name = \"trade.max.users\", defaultValue = \"50\")\n    53→    int maxUsers;\n    54→\n    55→    @Inject\n    56→    @ConfigProperty(name = \"trade.max.quotes\", defaultValue = \"100\")\n    57→    int maxQuotes;\n    58→\n    59→    @PostConstruct\n    60→    @TransactionAttribute(TransactionAttributeType.REQUIRED)\n    61→    void onStart() {\n    62→        if (!populateOnStartup) {\n    63→            Log.log(\"Database population disabled via configuration\");\n    64→            return;\n    65→        }\n    66→\n    67→        try {\n    68→            Number quoteCount = (Number) em.createNativeQuery(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM quoteejb\").getSingleResult();\n    69→            if (quoteCount.longValue() > 0) {\n    70→                Log.log(\"Database already populated with \" + quoteCount + \" quotes. Skipping population.\");\n    71→                return;\n    72→            }\n    73→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    74→            // Table may not exist yet, proceed with population\n    75→            Log.log(\"Database tables may not exist yet, proceeding with population...\");\n    76→        }\n    77→\n    78→        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Populating DayTrader Database on startup...\");\n    79→\n    80→        try {\n    81→            populateQuotes();\n    82→            populateUsers();\n    83→            Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Database population complete!\");\n    84→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    85→            Log.error(e, \"TradeBuildDB: Error populating database\");\n    86→        }\n    87→    }\n    88→\n    89→    private void populateQuotes() {\n    90→        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Creating \" + maxQuotes + \" Quotes...\");\n    91→\n    92→        for (int i = 0; i < maxQuotes; i++) {\n    93→            String symbol = \"s:\" + i;\n    94→            String companyName = \"S\" + i + \" Incorporated\";\n    95→            BigDecimal price = new BigDecimal(TradeConfig.rndPrice());\n    96→\n    97→            QuoteDataBean quote = new QuoteDataBean();\n    98→            quote.setSymbol(symbol);\n    99→            quote.setCompanyName(companyName);\n   100→            quote.setPrice(price);\n   101→            quote.setOpen(price);\n   102→            quote.setLow(price);\n   103→            quote.setHigh(price);\n   104→            quote.setChange(0.0);\n   105→            quote.setVolume(0.0);\n   106→\n   107→            em.persist(quote);\n   108→\n   109→            if (i % 10 == 0) {\n   110→                Log.log(\"Created quote: \" + symbol);\n   111→            }\n   112→        }\n   113→        em.flush();\n   114→    }\n   115→\n   116→    private void populateUsers() {\n   117→        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Registering \" + maxUsers + \" Users...\");\n   118→\n   119→        for (int i = 0; i < maxUsers; i++) {\n   120→            String userID = \"uid:\" + i;\n   121→            String fullname = TradeConfig.rndFullName();\n   122→            String email = TradeConfig.rndEmail(userID);\n   123→            String address = TradeConfig.rndAddress();\n   124→            String creditcard = TradeConfig.rndCreditCard();\n   125→            BigDecimal initialBalance = new BigDecimal((double) (TradeConfig.rndInt(100000)) + 200000);\n   126→\n   127→            if (i == 0) {\n   128→                initialBalance = new BigDecimal(1000000);\n   129→            }\n   130→\n   131→            AccountProfileDataBean profile = new AccountProfileDataBean();\n   132→            profile.setUserID(userID);\n   133→            profile.setPassword(\"xxx\");\n   134→            profile.setFullName(fullname);\n   135→            profile.setAddress(address);\n   136→            profile.setEmail(email);\n   137→            profile.setCreditCard(creditcard);\n   138→            em.persist(profile);\n   139→\n   140→            AccountDataBean account = new AccountDataBean();\n   141→            account.setProfile(profile);\n   142→            account.setCreationDate(new java.sql.Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n   143→            account.setLastLogin(new java.sql.Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n   144→            account.setBalance(initialBalance);\n   145→            account.setOpenBalance(initialBalance);\n   146→            account.setLoginCount(0);\n   147→            account.setLogoutCount(0);\n   148→            em.persist(account);\n   149→\n   150→            if (i % 10 == 0) {\n   151→                Log.log(\"Registered user: \" + userID + \" with balance: \" + initialBalance);\n   152→            }\n   153→        }\n   154→        em.flush();\n   155→    }\n   156→}\n   157→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YNn66n2h4yBgnSbLqJ6KDJ","session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"2f3b7806-de89-48b3-a2ba-b1d3575af194"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WPsRF7cW3JuFk4XkHfp3Zw","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/ejb3/MarketSummarySingleton.java has been updated. Here's the result of running `cat -n` on a snippet of the edited file:\n     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.ejb3;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    20→import java.util.List;\n    21→\n    22→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n    23→import jakarta.ejb.Lock;\n    24→import jakarta.ejb.LockType;\n    25→import jakarta.ejb.Schedule;\n    26→import jakarta.ejb.Singleton;\n    27→import jakarta.enterprise.event.Event;\n    28→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    29→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n    30→import jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n    31→import jakarta.persistence.TypedQuery;\n    32→import jakarta.persistence.criteria.CriteriaBuilder;\n    33→import jakarta.persistence.criteria.CriteriaQuery;\n    34→import jakarta.persistence.criteria.Root;\n    35→\n    36→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.MarketSummaryDataBean;\n    37→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    38→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.MarketSummaryUpdate;\n    39→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.FinancialUtils;\n    40→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    41→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    42→\n    43→@Singleton\n    44→public class MarketSummarySingleton {\n    45→\n    46→    private volatile MarketSummaryDataBean marketSummaryDataBean;\n    47→\n    48→    @PersistenceContext(unitName = \"daytrader\")\n    49→    EntityManager entityManager;\n    50→\n    51→    @Inject\n    52→    @MarketSummaryUpdate\n    53→    Event<String> mkSummaryUpdateEvent;\n    54→\n    55→    @PostConstruct\n    56→    void init() {\n    57→        Log.trace(\"MarketSummarySingleton:init()\");\n    58→    }\n    59→\n    60→    @Schedule(second = \"*/20\", minute = \"*\", hour = \"*\", persistent = false)\n    61→    void updateMarketSummary() {\n    62→        Log.trace(\"MarketSummarySingleton:updateMarketSummary -- updating market summary\");\n    63→\n    64→        if (TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode() != TradeConfig.EJB3) {\n    65→            Log.trace(\"MarketSummarySingleton:updateMarketSummary -- Not EJB3 Mode, so not updating periodically\");\n    66→            return;\n    67→        }\n    68→\n    69→        computeMarketSummary();\n    70→        try {\n    71→            mkSummaryUpdateEvent.fireAsync(\"MarketSummaryUpdate\");\n    72→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    73→            Log.trace(\"MarketSummarySingleton:updateMarketSummary -- async event fire failed (non-critical): \" + e.getMessage());\n    74→        }\n    75→    }\n    76→\n    77→    @Lock(LockType.READ)\n    78→    public MarketSummaryDataBean getMarketSummaryDataBean() {\n    79→        if (marketSummaryDataBean == null) {\n    80→            computeMarketSummary();\n    81→        }\n    82→        return marketSummaryDataBean;\n    83→    }\n    84→\n    85→    private void computeMarketSummary() {\n    86→        List<QuoteDataBean> quotes;\n    87→\n    88→        try {\n    89→            CriteriaBuilder criteriaBuilder = entityManager.getCriteriaBuilder();\n    90→            CriteriaQuery<QuoteDataBean> criteriaQuery = criteriaBuilder.createQuery(QuoteDataBean.class);\n    91→            Root<QuoteDataBean> quoteRoot = criteriaQuery.from(QuoteDataBean.class);\n    92→            criteriaQuery.orderBy(criteriaBuilder.desc(quoteRoot.get(\"change1\")));\n    93→            criteriaQuery.select(quoteRoot);\n    94→            TypedQuery<QuoteDataBean> q = entityManager.createQuery(criteriaQuery);\n    95→            quotes = q.getResultList();\n    96→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    97→            Log.debug(\"Warning: The database has not been configured. If this is the first time the application has been started, please create and populate the database tables. Then restart the server.\");\n    98→            return;\n    99→        }\n   100→\n   101→        QuoteDataBean[] quoteArray = quotes.toArray(new QuoteDataBean[quotes.size()]);\n   102→        ArrayList<QuoteDataBean> topGainers = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>(5);\n   103→        ArrayList<QuoteDataBean> topLosers = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>(5);\n   104→        BigDecimal TSIA = FinancialUtils.ZERO;\n   105→        BigDecimal openTSIA = FinancialUtils.ZERO;\n   106→        double totalVolume = 0.0;\n   107→\n   108→        if (quoteArray.length > 5) {\n   109→            for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {\n   110→                topGainers.add(quoteArray[i]);\n   111→            }\n   112→            for (int i = quoteArray.length - 1; i >= quoteArray.length - 5; i--) {\n   113→                topLosers.add(quoteArray[i]);\n   114→            }\n   115→\n   116→            for (QuoteDataBean quote : quoteArray) {\n   117→                BigDecimal price = quote.getPrice();\n   118→                BigDecimal open = quote.getOpen();\n   119→                double volume = quote.getVolume();\n   120→                TSIA = TSIA.add(price);\n   121→                openTSIA = openTSIA.add(open);\n   122→                totalVolume += volume;\n   123→            }\n   124→            TSIA = TSIA.divide(new BigDecimal(quoteArray.length), FinancialUtils.ROUND);\n   125→            openTSIA = openTSIA.divide(new BigDecimal(quoteArray.length), FinancialUtils.ROUND);\n   126→        }\n   127→\n   128→        setMarketSummaryDataBean(new MarketSummaryDataBean(TSIA, openTSIA, totalVolume, topGainers, topLosers));\n   129→    }\n   130→\n   131→    @Lock(LockType.WRITE)\n   132→    public void setMarketSummaryDataBean(MarketSummaryDataBean marketSummaryDataBean) {\n   133→        this.marketSummaryDataBean = marketSummaryDataBean;\n   134→    }\n   135→}\n   136→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YNn66n2h4yBgnSbLqJ6KDJ","session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"bc9b0cba-3d08-42a4-a05b-396f9a4a7e67"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YNn66n2h4yBgnSbLqJ6KDJ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! All three files have been successfully migrated from Quarkus to Jakarta EE. Let me summarize the changes made:\n\n## Migration Summary\n\nI've successfully migrated all three files from Quarkus to Jakarta EE (Open Liberty) with the following changes:\n\n### 1. **DatabasePopulator.java**\n**Location:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/startup/DatabasePopulator.java`\n\n**Key Changes:**\n- Changed from `@ApplicationScoped` with `@Observes StartupEvent` to `@Singleton` with `@Startup` EJB pattern\n- Replaced `io.quarkus.runtime.StartupEvent` with Jakarta EE `@PostConstruct` lifecycle callback\n- Changed `@Inject EntityManager` to `@PersistenceContext(unitName = \"daytrader\") EntityManager`\n- Added `@TransactionAttribute(TransactionAttributeType.REQUIRED)` for transaction management\n- Removed Quarkus-specific `@Transactional` in favor of EJB transaction attributes\n\n### 2. **MarketSummarySingleton.java**\n**Location:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/ejb3/MarketSummarySingleton.java`\n\n**Key Changes:**\n- Changed from `@ApplicationScoped` with Quarkus `@Scheduled` to `@Singleton` with Jakarta EE `@Schedule`\n- Replaced `io.quarkus.scheduler.Scheduled(every = \"20s\")` with `@Schedule(second = \"*/20\", minute = \"*\", hour = \"*\", persistent = false)`\n- Changed from `synchronized` methods to proper EJB `@Lock` annotations (`@Lock(LockType.READ)` and `@Lock(LockType.WRITE)`)\n- Changed `@Inject EntityManager` to `@PersistenceContext(unitName = \"daytrader\") EntityManager`\n- Added `@PostConstruct` for initialization\n- Added error handling for async event firing\n\n### 3. **TradeSLSBBean.java**\n**Location:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/impl/ejb3/TradeSLSBBean.java`\n\n**Key Changes:**\n- Changed `@Inject EntityManager entityManager;` to `@PersistenceContext(unitName = \"daytrader\") EntityManager entityManager;`\n- All other Jakarta EE annotations remained the same as they were already using standard `jakarta.*` imports\n- Preserved all existing `@ApplicationScoped`, `@Transactional`, and CDI qualifiers\n\nAll files now use standard Jakarta EE APIs compatible with Open Liberty, removing all Quarkus-specific dependencies (`io.quarkus.runtime.StartupEvent`, `io.quarkus.scheduler.Scheduled`)."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"86f8530c-26c8-49ac-a9a9-87a14a5d3698"}
