{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015cWqPrgDUsFnbbs7CRAzPv","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015, 2024.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.startup;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→\n    20→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n    21→import jakarta.ejb.Singleton;\n    22→import jakarta.ejb.Startup;\n    23→import jakarta.ejb.TransactionAttribute;\n    24→import jakarta.ejb.TransactionAttributeType;\n    25→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    26→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n    27→import jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n    28→\n    29→import org.eclipse.microprofile.config.inject.ConfigProperty;\n    30→\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n    32→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\n    33→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    35→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    36→\n    37→/**\n    38→ * Populates the database with initial data on application startup.\n    39→ */\n    40→@Singleton\n    41→@Startup\n    42→public class DatabasePopulator {\n    43→\n    44→    @PersistenceContext(unitName = \"daytrader\")\n    45→    EntityManager em;\n    46→\n    47→    @Inject\n    48→    @ConfigProperty(name = \"trade.db.populate.on.startup\", defaultValue = \"true\")\n    49→    boolean populateOnStartup;\n    50→\n    51→    @Inject\n    52→    @ConfigProperty(name = \"trade.max.users\", defaultValue = \"50\")\n    53→    int maxUsers;\n    54→\n    55→    @Inject\n    56→    @ConfigProperty(name = \"trade.max.quotes\", defaultValue = \"100\")\n    57→    int maxQuotes;\n    58→\n    59→    @PostConstruct\n    60→    @TransactionAttribute(TransactionAttributeType.REQUIRED)\n    61→    void onStart() {\n    62→        if (!populateOnStartup) {\n    63→            Log.log(\"Database population disabled via configuration\");\n    64→            return;\n    65→        }\n    66→\n    67→        try {\n    68→            Number quoteCount = (Number) em.createNativeQuery(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM quoteejb\").getSingleResult();\n    69→            if (quoteCount.longValue() > 0) {\n    70→                Log.log(\"Database already populated with \" + quoteCount + \" quotes. Skipping population.\");\n    71→                return;\n    72→            }\n    73→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    74→            // Table may not exist yet, proceed with population\n    75→            Log.log(\"Database tables may not exist yet, proceeding with population...\");\n    76→        }\n    77→\n    78→        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Populating DayTrader Database on startup...\");\n    79→\n    80→        try {\n    81→            populateQuotes();\n    82→            populateUsers();\n    83→            Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Database population complete!\");\n    84→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    85→            Log.error(e, \"TradeBuildDB: Error populating database\");\n    86→        }\n    87→    }\n    88→\n    89→    private void populateQuotes() {\n    90→        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Creating \" + maxQuotes + \" Quotes...\");\n    91→\n    92→        for (int i = 0; i < maxQuotes; i++) {\n    93→            String symbol = \"s:\" + i;\n    94→            String companyName = \"S\" + i + \" Incorporated\";\n    95→            BigDecimal price = new BigDecimal(TradeConfig.rndPrice());\n    96→\n    97→            QuoteDataBean quote = new QuoteDataBean();\n    98→            quote.setSymbol(symbol);\n    99→            quote.setCompanyName(companyName);\n   100→            quote.setPrice(price);\n   101→            quote.setOpen(price);\n   102→            quote.setLow(price);\n   103→            quote.setHigh(price);\n   104→            quote.setChange(0.0);\n   105→            quote.setVolume(0.0);\n   106→\n   107→            em.persist(quote);\n   108→\n   109→            if (i % 10 == 0) {\n   110→                Log.log(\"Created quote: \" + symbol);\n   111→            }\n   112→        }\n   113→        em.flush();\n   114→    }\n   115→\n   116→    private void populateUsers() {\n   117→        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Registering \" + maxUsers + \" Users...\");\n   118→\n   119→        for (int i = 0; i < maxUsers; i++) {\n   120→            String userID = \"uid:\" + i;\n   121→            String fullname = TradeConfig.rndFullName();\n   122→            String email = TradeConfig.rndEmail(userID);\n   123→            String address = TradeConfig.rndAddress();\n   124→            String creditcard = TradeConfig.rndCreditCard();\n   125→            BigDecimal initialBalance = new BigDecimal((double) (TradeConfig.rndInt(100000)) + 200000);\n   126→\n   127→            if (i == 0) {\n   128→                initialBalance = new BigDecimal(1000000);\n   129→            }\n   130→\n   131→            AccountProfileDataBean profile = new AccountProfileDataBean();\n   132→            profile.setUserID(userID);\n   133→            profile.setPassword(\"xxx\");\n   134→            profile.setFullName(fullname);\n   135→            profile.setAddress(address);\n   136→            profile.setEmail(email);\n   137→            profile.setCreditCard(creditcard);\n   138→            em.persist(profile);\n   139→\n   140→            AccountDataBean account = new AccountDataBean();\n   141→            account.setProfile(profile);\n   142→            account.setCreationDate(new java.sql.Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n   143→            account.setLastLogin(new java.sql.Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n   144→            account.setBalance(initialBalance);\n   145→            account.setOpenBalance(initialBalance);\n   146→            account.setLoginCount(0);\n   147→            account.setLogoutCount(0);\n   148→            em.persist(account);\n   149→\n   150→            if (i % 10 == 0) {\n   151→                Log.log(\"Registered user: \" + userID + \" with balance: \" + initialBalance);\n   152→            }\n   153→        }\n   154→        em.flush();\n   155→    }\n   156→}\n   157→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"ec404153-ced5-4d63-8181-bfc58334d9c6"}
