{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01WzfPoc1qaK1umXGjJHqB5q","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"There are two issues:\n1. The DataSource still seems to have issues (the prepareStatement error indicates the connection URL might still be wrong)\n2. The DatabasePopulator `@PostConstruct` is failing because it catches an exception during the initial count query, which causes the transaction to be rolled back, and Liberty doesn't allow setRollbackOnly in a singleton PostConstruct.\n\nLet me look at the earlier errors to understand the DataSource issue:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2215,"cache_read_input_tokens":129534,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2215,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":204},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"beb0ea72-4cff-4ec9-826a-9389a647ae3f"}
