{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01L2aZqqdatLQXED6qG4WZuY","type":"tool_result","content":"[INFO    ] DSRA8203I: Database product name : H2\n[INFO    ] DSRA8204I: Database product version : 2.2.224 (2023-09-17)\n[INFO    ] DSRA8205I: JDBC driver name  : H2 JDBC Driver\n[INFO    ] DSRA8206I: JDBC driver version  : 2.2.224 (2023-09-17)\n[WARNING ] CWWJP9991W: Exception [EclipseLink-4002] (Eclipse Persistence Services - 4.0.9.v202601021151-061974965b9a70b72fdcb96dae36a4d6ef5df9ce): org.eclipse.persistence.exceptions.DatabaseException\nInternal Exception: org.h2.jdbc.JdbcSQLSyntaxErrorException: Table \"ACCOUNTEJB\" not found; SQL statement:\n[WARNING ] CWWJP9991W: Exception [EclipseLink-4002] (Eclipse Persistence Services - 4.0.9.v202601021151-061974965b9a70b72fdcb96dae36a4d6ef5df9ce): org.eclipse.persistence.exceptions.DatabaseException\nInternal Exception: org.h2.jdbc.JdbcSQLSyntaxErrorException: Table \"HOLDINGEJB\" not found; SQL statement:\n[WARNING ] CWWJP9991W: Exception [EclipseLink-4002] (Eclipse Persistence Services - 4.0.9.v202601021151-061974965b9a70b72fdcb96dae36a4d6ef5df9ce): org.eclipse.persistence.exceptions.DatabaseException\nInternal Exception: org.h2.jdbc.JdbcSQLSyntaxErrorException: Table \"HOLDINGEJB\" not found; SQL statement:\n[WARNING ] CWWJP9991W: Exception [EclipseLink-4002] (Eclipse Persistence Services - 4.0.9.v202601021151-061974965b9a70b72fdcb96dae36a4d6ef5df9ce): org.eclipse.persistence.exceptions.DatabaseException\nInternal Exception: org.h2.jdbc.JdbcSQLSyntaxErrorException: Table \"ORDEREJB\" not found; SQL statement:\n[WARNING ] CWWJP9991W: Exception [EclipseLink-4002] (Eclipse Persistence Services - 4.0.9.v202601021151-061974965b9a70b72fdcb96dae36a4d6ef5df9ce): org.eclipse.persistence.exceptions.DatabaseException\nInternal Exception: org.h2.jdbc.JdbcSQLSyntaxErrorException: Table \"ORDEREJB\" not found; SQL statement:\n[WARNING ] CWWJP9991W: Exception [EclipseLink-4002] (Eclipse Persistence Services - 4.0.9.v202601021151-061974965b9a70b72fdcb96dae36a4d6ef5df9ce): org.eclipse.persistence.exceptions.DatabaseException\nInternal Exception: org.h2.jdbc.JdbcSQLSyntaxErrorException: Table \"ORDEREJB\" not found; SQL statement:\n[WARNING ] CWWJP9991W: Exception [EclipseLink-4002] (Eclipse Persistence Services - 4.0.9.v202601021151-061974965b9a70b72fdcb96dae36a4d6ef5df9ce): org.eclipse.persistence.exceptions.DatabaseException\nInternal Exception: org.h2.jdbc.JdbcSQLSyntaxErrorException: Table \"ACCOUNTEJB\" not found; SQL statement:\n[WARNING ] CWWJP9991W: Exception [EclipseLink-4002] (Eclipse Persistence Services - 4.0.9.v202601021151-061974965b9a70b72fdcb96dae36a4d6ef5df9ce): org.eclipse.persistence.exceptions.DatabaseException\nInternal Exception: org.h2.jdbc.JdbcSQLSyntaxErrorException: Table \"ACCOUNTPROFILEEJB\" not found; SQL statement:","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"de7fcf8a-d023-4be5-b184-78e88a82396d"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01KTuTWBfx5f4tmnE9SpbH2T","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The DataSource connection is working now (H2 is detected). The issue is:\n\n1. The `drop-and-create` schema generation drops tables first (generating \"table not found\" warnings which are expected), then creates them\n2. But the DatabasePopulator's `@PostConstruct` runs a native SQL `SELECT COUNT(*) FROM quoteejb` which fails because the table doesn't exist yet at that point (or the timing is off with the drop-and-create)\n3. The exception gets caught, but it marks the transaction for rollback, and Liberty doesn't allow that in singleton PostConstruct\n\nThe fix is to make the DatabasePopulator use Bean-Managed Transactions (BMT) so we can control the transaction boundary, or to use a different approach. Let me fix the DatabasePopulator:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1442,"cache_read_input_tokens":131749,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1442,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1994},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"9c0a1b38-3d7e-4f54-883c-4f1a115c8401"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01KTuTWBfx5f4tmnE9SpbH2T","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01DcVKvcmQsex99RgEhhKo2i","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/startup/DatabasePopulator.java","content":"/**\n * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015, 2024.\n *\n * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n *\n * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n *\n * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n * limitations under the License.\n */\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.startup;\n\nimport java.math.BigDecimal;\n\nimport jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\nimport jakarta.annotation.Resource;\nimport jakarta.ejb.Singleton;\nimport jakarta.ejb.Startup;\nimport jakarta.ejb.TransactionManagement;\nimport jakarta.ejb.TransactionManagementType;\nimport jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\nimport jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\nimport jakarta.transaction.UserTransaction;\n\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.config.inject.ConfigProperty;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\n\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n\n/**\n * Populates the database with initial data on application startup.\n * Uses Bean-Managed Transactions to avoid issues with singleton PostConstruct\n * transaction rollback on Open Liberty.\n */\n@Singleton\n@Startup\n@TransactionManagement(TransactionManagementType.BEAN)\npublic class DatabasePopulator {\n\n    @PersistenceContext(unitName = \"daytrader\")\n    EntityManager em;\n\n    @Resource\n    UserTransaction utx;\n\n    @Inject\n    @ConfigProperty(name = \"trade.db.populate.on.startup\", defaultValue = \"true\")\n    boolean populateOnStartup;\n\n    @Inject\n    @ConfigProperty(name = \"trade.max.users\", defaultValue = \"50\")\n    int maxUsers;\n\n    @Inject\n    @ConfigProperty(name = \"trade.max.quotes\", defaultValue = \"100\")\n    int maxQuotes;\n\n    @PostConstruct\n    void onStart() {\n        if (!populateOnStartup) {\n            Log.log(\"Database population disabled via configuration\");\n            return;\n        }\n\n        // Check if database already has data\n        try {\n            utx.begin();\n            Number quoteCount = (Number) em.createNativeQuery(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM quoteejb\").getSingleResult();\n            utx.commit();\n            if (quoteCount.longValue() > 0) {\n                Log.log(\"Database already populated with \" + quoteCount + \" quotes. Skipping population.\");\n                return;\n            }\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            // Table may not exist yet or other issue, try to rollback and proceed\n            try { utx.rollback(); } catch (Exception re) { /* ignore */ }\n            Log.log(\"Database tables may be newly created, proceeding with population...\");\n        }\n\n        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Populating DayTrader Database on startup...\");\n\n        try {\n            utx.begin();\n            populateQuotes();\n            populateUsers();\n            utx.commit();\n            Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Database population complete!\");\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            try { utx.rollback(); } catch (Exception re) { /* ignore */ }\n            Log.error(e, \"TradeBuildDB: Error populating database\");\n        }\n    }\n\n    private void populateQuotes() {\n        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Creating \" + maxQuotes + \" Quotes...\");\n\n        for (int i = 0; i < maxQuotes; i++) {\n            String symbol = \"s:\" + i;\n            String companyName = \"S\" + i + \" Incorporated\";\n            BigDecimal price = new BigDecimal(TradeConfig.rndPrice());\n\n            QuoteDataBean quote = new QuoteDataBean();\n            quote.setSymbol(symbol);\n            quote.setCompanyName(companyName);\n            quote.setPrice(price);\n            quote.setOpen(price);\n            quote.setLow(price);\n            quote.setHigh(price);\n            quote.setChange(0.0);\n            quote.setVolume(0.0);\n\n            em.persist(quote);\n\n            if (i % 10 == 0) {\n                Log.log(\"Created quote: \" + symbol);\n            }\n        }\n        em.flush();\n    }\n\n    private void populateUsers() {\n        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Registering \" + maxUsers + \" Users...\");\n\n        for (int i = 0; i < maxUsers; i++) {\n            String userID = \"uid:\" + i;\n            String fullname = TradeConfig.rndFullName();\n            String email = TradeConfig.rndEmail(userID);\n            String address = TradeConfig.rndAddress();\n            String creditcard = TradeConfig.rndCreditCard();\n            BigDecimal initialBalance = new BigDecimal((double) (TradeConfig.rndInt(100000)) + 200000);\n\n            if (i == 0) {\n                initialBalance = new BigDecimal(1000000);\n            }\n\n            AccountProfileDataBean profile = new AccountProfileDataBean();\n            profile.setUserID(userID);\n            profile.setPassword(\"xxx\");\n            profile.setFullName(fullname);\n            profile.setAddress(address);\n            profile.setEmail(email);\n            profile.setCreditCard(creditcard);\n            em.persist(profile);\n\n            AccountDataBean account = new AccountDataBean();\n            account.setProfile(profile);\n            account.setCreationDate(new java.sql.Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n            account.setLastLogin(new java.sql.Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n            account.setBalance(initialBalance);\n            account.setOpenBalance(initialBalance);\n            account.setLoginCount(0);\n            account.setLogoutCount(0);\n            em.persist(account);\n\n            if (i % 10 == 0) {\n                Log.log(\"Registered user: \" + userID + \" with balance: \" + initialBalance);\n            }\n        }\n        em.flush();\n    }\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1442,"cache_read_input_tokens":131749,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1442,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1994},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"10a2d1cd-86b6-4e20-aac7-e98d92ed6184"}
