{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_017hynTKdqRgDgXBhAoyQoab","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The application has started successfully (`Application daytrader started in 3.058 seconds` and `The defaultServer server is ready`). However, the database population failed because the tables aren't being created. The `drop-and-create` schema generation doesn't seem to be working with EclipseLink on Liberty.\n\nThe issue is that EclipseLink's `drop-and-create` happens during EMF creation, but with `@TransactionManagement(TransactionManagementType.BEAN)` and the way Open Liberty processes things, the tables might not be created yet. Let me check if the table creation is working at all by looking at the API:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2622,"cache_read_input_tokens":138952,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2622,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":269},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"97c67488-e9ca-4483-925a-94d2e14baed8"}
