{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YNhrJmpnZNX1sbJjy4un7D","type":"tool_result","content":"[INFO    ] CWWKS4105I: LTPA configuration is ready after 0.021 seconds.\n[INFO    ] CWWKS0008I: The security service is ready.\nInternal Exception: org.h2.jdbc.JdbcSQLSyntaxErrorException: Table \"ACCOUNTEJB\" not found; SQL statement:\nError Code: 42102\nInternal Exception: org.h2.jdbc.JdbcSQLSyntaxErrorException: Table \"HOLDINGEJB\" not found; SQL statement:\nError Code: 42102\nInternal Exception: org.h2.jdbc.JdbcSQLSyntaxErrorException: Table \"HOLDINGEJB\" not found; SQL statement:\nError Code: 42102\nInternal Exception: org.h2.jdbc.JdbcSQLSyntaxErrorException: Table \"ORDEREJB\" not found; SQL statement:\nError Code: 42102\nInternal Exception: org.h2.jdbc.JdbcSQLSyntaxErrorException: Table \"ORDEREJB\" not found; SQL statement:\nError Code: 42102\nInternal Exception: org.h2.jdbc.JdbcSQLSyntaxErrorException: Table \"ORDEREJB\" not found; SQL statement:\nError Code: 42102\nInternal Exception: org.h2.jdbc.JdbcSQLSyntaxErrorException: Table \"ACCOUNTEJB\" not found; SQL statement:\nError Code: 42102\nInternal Exception: org.h2.jdbc.JdbcSQLSyntaxErrorException: Table \"ACCOUNTPROFILEEJB\" not found; SQL statement:\nError Code: 42102\nInternal Exception: org.h2.jdbc.JdbcSQLSyntaxErrorException: Table \"HOLDINGEJB\" not found; SQL statement:\nError Code: 42102\nInternal Exception: org.h2.jdbc.JdbcSQLSyntaxErrorException: Table \"ORDEREJB\" not found; SQL statement:\nError Code: 42102\nInternal Exception: org.h2.jdbc.JdbcSQLSyntaxErrorException: Table \"QUOTEEJB\" not found; SQL statement:\nError Code: 42102\nInternal Exception: org.h2.jdbc.JdbcSQLSyntaxErrorException: Table \"ACCOUNTEJB\" not found; SQL statement:","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"f5bd614f-8ba3-4fc9-9c01-72e9014b85d4"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_015iokpV3qHFXuzh73eE2etF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The EclipseLink DDL generation is not creating ANY tables! The issue is that `create-tables` first tries to run ALTER TABLE FK constraints (which fail because the referenced tables don't exist yet), and this somehow prevents the CREATE TABLE statements. This seems to be an EclipseLink behavior issue with H2 and FK constraints order.\n\nLet me try a more direct approach - I'll have the tables created via JDBC before JPA initialization happens. Looking at the order of events, the @Startup singleton needs to create tables first via JDBC, then use JPA. The key insight is: the JDBC and JPA connections share the same H2 in-memory database, so tables created via JDBC should be visible to JPA.\n\nWait - the previous attempt where I used JDBC to create ALL tables (including accountejb) succeeded at creating them, AND quotes were populated successfully via JPA. But accountejb inserts failed. This suggests the issue might be with the AccountDataBean entity mapping specifically. Let me check the entity:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":933,"cache_read_input_tokens":149863,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":933,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":386},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"add48457-e2f7-410f-ab57-18703b44c0bf"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_015iokpV3qHFXuzh73eE2etF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01V1pqTB7m4mAmQDsZf3sS2n","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/entities/AccountDataBean.java","offset":40,"limit":55}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":933,"cache_read_input_tokens":149863,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":933,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":386},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"abc0e397-65d8-4cbd-a2c7-529e220ff4fe"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01V1pqTB7m4mAmQDsZf3sS2n","type":"tool_result","content":"    40→\n    41→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonIgnore;\n    42→\n    43→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    44→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    45→\n    46→@Entity(name = \"accountejb\")\n    47→@Table(name = \"accountejb\")\n    48→public class AccountDataBean implements Serializable {\n    49→\n    50→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 8437841265136840545L;\n    51→\n    52→    // MIGRATION: Simplified ID generation - Quarkus/Hibernate handles this better with IDENTITY\n    53→    @Id\n    54→    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.IDENTITY)\n    55→    @Column(name = \"ACCOUNTID\", nullable = false)\n    56→    private Integer accountID;\n    57→\n    58→    @NotNull\n    59→    @PositiveOrZero\n    60→    @Column(name = \"LOGINCOUNT\", nullable = false)\n    61→    private int loginCount;\n    62→\n    63→    @NotNull\n    64→    @PositiveOrZero\n    65→    @Column(name = \"LOGOUTCOUNT\", nullable = false)\n    66→    private int logoutCount;\n    67→\n    68→    @Column(name = \"LASTLOGIN\")\n    69→    @Temporal(TemporalType.TIMESTAMP)\n    70→    @PastOrPresent\n    71→    private Date lastLogin;\n    72→\n    73→    @Column(name = \"CREATIONDATE\")\n    74→    @Temporal(TemporalType.TIMESTAMP)\n    75→    @PastOrPresent\n    76→    private Date creationDate;\n    77→\n    78→    @Column(name = \"BALANCE\")\n    79→    private BigDecimal balance;\n    80→\n    81→    @Column(name = \"OPENBALANCE\")\n    82→    private BigDecimal openBalance;\n    83→\n    84→    @JsonIgnore\n    85→    @OneToMany(mappedBy = \"account\", fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    86→    private Collection<OrderDataBean> orders;\n    87→\n    88→    @JsonIgnore\n    89→    @OneToMany(mappedBy = \"account\", fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    90→    private Collection<HoldingDataBean> holdings;\n    91→\n    92→    @JsonIgnore\n    93→    @OneToOne(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    94→    @JoinColumn(name = \"PROFILE_USERID\")\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"f7273d52-da98-4671-bcb0-9cbf5289295a"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01PPwuB9e88VCAUebzzp6ws7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I see. The entity uses `@JsonIgnore` from Jackson and `@OneToMany`/`@OneToOne` with various relationships. The EclipseLink issue is with DDL generation.\n\nLet me go back to the approach that was partially working (JDBC table creation + JPA population) and think about WHY the JDBC-created `accountejb` table isn't visible to JPA. The answer is: When we use `@TransactionManagement(TransactionManagementType.BEAN)`, the JDBC connection for table creation uses `conn.setAutoCommit(true)` which means it commits immediately. But the JPA EntityManager uses a separate connection from the container pool. In H2 with `mem:tradedb;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1`, both should see the same database.\n\nActually, the REAL issue may be that Open Liberty's `@Resource(lookup = \"jdbc/TradeDataSource\") DataSource` for JDBC returns a connection from a _different_ pool or wrapper than what EclipseLink's JTA DataSource uses. This is actually a known issue with Liberty.\n\nLet me change strategy: instead of JDBC table creation, let me use JPA's native query to create the tables:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1157,"cache_read_input_tokens":150796,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1157,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3017},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"9ce1757c-067f-412b-b0d3-d49854fe6718"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01PPwuB9e88VCAUebzzp6ws7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01KFyP9ymXRoeKwGYfj8CWMN","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/startup/DatabasePopulator.java","content":"/**\n * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015, 2024.\n */\npackage com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.startup;\n\nimport java.math.BigDecimal;\n\nimport jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\nimport jakarta.annotation.Resource;\nimport jakarta.ejb.Singleton;\nimport jakarta.ejb.Startup;\nimport jakarta.ejb.TransactionManagement;\nimport jakarta.ejb.TransactionManagementType;\nimport jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\nimport jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\nimport jakarta.transaction.UserTransaction;\n\nimport org.eclipse.microprofile.config.inject.ConfigProperty;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\n\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\nimport com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n\n@Singleton\n@Startup\n@TransactionManagement(TransactionManagementType.BEAN)\npublic class DatabasePopulator {\n\n    @PersistenceContext(unitName = \"daytrader\")\n    EntityManager em;\n\n    @Resource\n    UserTransaction utx;\n\n    @Inject\n    @ConfigProperty(name = \"trade.db.populate.on.startup\", defaultValue = \"true\")\n    boolean populateOnStartup;\n\n    @Inject\n    @ConfigProperty(name = \"trade.max.users\", defaultValue = \"50\")\n    int maxUsers;\n\n    @Inject\n    @ConfigProperty(name = \"trade.max.quotes\", defaultValue = \"100\")\n    int maxQuotes;\n\n    @PostConstruct\n    void onStart() {\n        if (!populateOnStartup) {\n            Log.log(\"Database population disabled via configuration\");\n            return;\n        }\n\n        // Create tables using JPA native queries (same connection pool as JPA)\n        createTables();\n\n        // Check if database already has data\n        try {\n            utx.begin();\n            Number quoteCount = (Number) em.createNativeQuery(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM quoteejb\").getSingleResult();\n            utx.commit();\n            if (quoteCount.longValue() > 0) {\n                Log.log(\"Database already populated with \" + quoteCount + \" quotes. Skipping population.\");\n                return;\n            }\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            try { utx.rollback(); } catch (Exception re) { /* ignore */ }\n            Log.log(\"Proceeding with database population...\");\n        }\n\n        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Populating DayTrader Database on startup...\");\n\n        try {\n            utx.begin();\n            populateQuotes();\n            utx.commit();\n            Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Quotes populated successfully\");\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            try { utx.rollback(); } catch (Exception re) { /* ignore */ }\n            Log.error(e, \"TradeBuildDB: Error populating quotes\");\n            return;\n        }\n\n        try {\n            utx.begin();\n            populateUsers();\n            utx.commit();\n            Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Users populated successfully\");\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            try { utx.rollback(); } catch (Exception re) { /* ignore */ }\n            Log.error(e, \"TradeBuildDB: Error populating users\");\n            return;\n        }\n\n        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Database population complete!\");\n    }\n\n    private void createTables() {\n        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Creating database tables via JPA native queries...\");\n        try {\n            utx.begin();\n\n            em.createNativeQuery(\"CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS quoteejb (\"\n                + \"SYMBOL VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL PRIMARY KEY, \"\n                + \"COMPANYNAME VARCHAR(255), \"\n                + \"VOLUME DOUBLE NOT NULL, \"\n                + \"PRICE DECIMAL(14,2), \"\n                + \"OPEN1 DECIMAL(14,2), \"\n                + \"LOW DECIMAL(14,2), \"\n                + \"HIGH DECIMAL(14,2), \"\n                + \"CHANGE1 DOUBLE NOT NULL)\").executeUpdate();\n\n            em.createNativeQuery(\"CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS accountprofileejb (\"\n                + \"USERID VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL PRIMARY KEY, \"\n                + \"PASSWD VARCHAR(255), \"\n                + \"FULLNAME VARCHAR(255), \"\n                + \"ADDRESS VARCHAR(255), \"\n                + \"EMAIL VARCHAR(255), \"\n                + \"CREDITCARD VARCHAR(255))\").executeUpdate();\n\n            em.createNativeQuery(\"CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS accountejb (\"\n                + \"ACCOUNTID INTEGER GENERATED BY DEFAULT AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY, \"\n                + \"LOGINCOUNT INTEGER NOT NULL, \"\n                + \"LOGOUTCOUNT INTEGER NOT NULL, \"\n                + \"LASTLOGIN TIMESTAMP, \"\n                + \"CREATIONDATE TIMESTAMP, \"\n                + \"BALANCE DECIMAL(14,2), \"\n                + \"OPENBALANCE DECIMAL(14,2), \"\n                + \"PROFILE_USERID VARCHAR(255), \"\n                + \"CONSTRAINT FK_ACCT_PROFILE FOREIGN KEY (PROFILE_USERID) REFERENCES accountprofileejb(USERID))\").executeUpdate();\n\n            em.createNativeQuery(\"CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS holdingejb (\"\n                + \"HOLDINGID INTEGER GENERATED BY DEFAULT AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY, \"\n                + \"QUANTITY DOUBLE NOT NULL, \"\n                + \"PURCHASEPRICE DECIMAL(14,2), \"\n                + \"PURCHASEDATE TIMESTAMP, \"\n                + \"ACCOUNT_ACCOUNTID INTEGER, \"\n                + \"QUOTE_SYMBOL VARCHAR(255), \"\n                + \"CONSTRAINT FK_HOLD_ACCT FOREIGN KEY (ACCOUNT_ACCOUNTID) REFERENCES accountejb(ACCOUNTID), \"\n                + \"CONSTRAINT FK_HOLD_QUOTE FOREIGN KEY (QUOTE_SYMBOL) REFERENCES quoteejb(SYMBOL))\").executeUpdate();\n\n            em.createNativeQuery(\"CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS orderejb (\"\n                + \"ORDERID INTEGER GENERATED BY DEFAULT AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY, \"\n                + \"ORDERTYPE VARCHAR(255), \"\n                + \"ORDERSTATUS VARCHAR(255), \"\n                + \"OPENDATE TIMESTAMP, \"\n                + \"COMPLETIONDATE TIMESTAMP, \"\n                + \"QUANTITY DOUBLE NOT NULL, \"\n                + \"PRICE DECIMAL(14,2), \"\n                + \"ORDERFEE DECIMAL(14,2), \"\n                + \"ACCOUNT_ACCOUNTID INTEGER, \"\n                + \"QUOTE_SYMBOL VARCHAR(255), \"\n                + \"HOLDING_HOLDINGID INTEGER, \"\n                + \"CONSTRAINT FK_ORD_ACCT FOREIGN KEY (ACCOUNT_ACCOUNTID) REFERENCES accountejb(ACCOUNTID), \"\n                + \"CONSTRAINT FK_ORD_QUOTE FOREIGN KEY (QUOTE_SYMBOL) REFERENCES quoteejb(SYMBOL), \"\n                + \"CONSTRAINT FK_ORD_HOLD FOREIGN KEY (HOLDING_HOLDINGID) REFERENCES holdingejb(HOLDINGID))\").executeUpdate();\n\n            em.createNativeQuery(\"CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS keygenejb (\"\n                + \"KEYNAME VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL PRIMARY KEY, \"\n                + \"KEYVAL INTEGER NOT NULL)\").executeUpdate();\n\n            utx.commit();\n            Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Database tables created successfully\");\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            try { utx.rollback(); } catch (Exception re) { /* ignore */ }\n            Log.error(e, \"TradeBuildDB: Error creating tables\");\n        }\n    }\n\n    private void populateQuotes() {\n        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Creating \" + maxQuotes + \" Quotes...\");\n        for (int i = 0; i < maxQuotes; i++) {\n            String symbol = \"s:\" + i;\n            String companyName = \"S\" + i + \" Incorporated\";\n            BigDecimal price = new BigDecimal(TradeConfig.rndPrice());\n\n            QuoteDataBean quote = new QuoteDataBean();\n            quote.setSymbol(symbol);\n            quote.setCompanyName(companyName);\n            quote.setPrice(price);\n            quote.setOpen(price);\n            quote.setLow(price);\n            quote.setHigh(price);\n            quote.setChange(0.0);\n            quote.setVolume(0.0);\n            em.persist(quote);\n            if (i % 10 == 0) Log.log(\"Created quote: \" + symbol);\n        }\n        em.flush();\n    }\n\n    private void populateUsers() {\n        Log.log(\"TradeBuildDB: Registering \" + maxUsers + \" Users...\");\n        for (int i = 0; i < maxUsers; i++) {\n            String userID = \"uid:\" + i;\n            String fullname = TradeConfig.rndFullName();\n            String email = TradeConfig.rndEmail(userID);\n            String address = TradeConfig.rndAddress();\n            String creditcard = TradeConfig.rndCreditCard();\n            BigDecimal initialBalance = new BigDecimal((double)(TradeConfig.rndInt(100000)) + 200000);\n            if (i == 0) initialBalance = new BigDecimal(1000000);\n\n            AccountProfileDataBean profile = new AccountProfileDataBean();\n            profile.setUserID(userID);\n            profile.setPassword(\"xxx\");\n            profile.setFullName(fullname);\n            profile.setAddress(address);\n            profile.setEmail(email);\n            profile.setCreditCard(creditcard);\n            em.persist(profile);\n\n            AccountDataBean account = new AccountDataBean();\n            account.setProfile(profile);\n            account.setCreationDate(new java.sql.Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n            account.setLastLogin(new java.sql.Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n            account.setBalance(initialBalance);\n            account.setOpenBalance(initialBalance);\n            account.setLoginCount(0);\n            account.setLogoutCount(0);\n            em.persist(account);\n            if (i % 10 == 0) Log.log(\"Registered user: \" + userID);\n        }\n        em.flush();\n    }\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1157,"cache_read_input_tokens":150796,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1157,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3017},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"8f670e0e-3a00-4817-b6d2-899e70f34d44"}
