abaseException\njakarta.persistence.PersistenceException: Exception [EclipseLink-4002] (Eclipse Persistence Services - 4.0.9.v202601021151-061974965b9a70b72fdcb96dae36a4d6ef5df9ce): org.eclipse.persistence.exceptions.DatabaseException\n\tat com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.startup.DatabasePopulator.populateUsers(DatabasePopulator.java:151)\n\tat com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.startup.DatabasePopulator.onStart(DatabasePopulator.java:76)\nException [EclipseLink-4002] (Eclipse Persistence Services - 4.0.9.v202601021151-061974965b9a70b72fdcb96dae36a4d6ef5df9ce): org.eclipse.persistence.exceptions.DatabaseException\njakarta.persistence.PersistenceException: Exception [EclipseLink-4002] (Eclipse Persistence Services - 4.0.9.v202601021151-061974965b9a70b72fdcb96dae36a4d6ef5df9ce): org.eclipse.persistence.exceptions.DatabaseException\n\tat com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.startup.DatabasePopulator.populateUsers(DatabasePopulator.java:151)\n\tat com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.startup.DatabasePopulator.onStart(DatabasePopulator.java:76)\nException [EclipseLink-4002] (Eclipse Persistence Services - 4.0.9.v202601021151-061974965b9a70b72fdcb96dae36a4d6ef5df9ce): org.eclipse.persistence.exceptions.DatabaseException","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"49aed08a-77ca-403c-b481-358b6084077d"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_014YUZAdcmY8PH3LXBxp4U9w","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I can see the root cause clearly. EclipseLink's DDL generation is using `INTEGER IDENTITY` syntax which H2 2.x doesn't support. H2 2.x requires `INTEGER GENERATED BY DEFAULT AS IDENTITY`. This is a compatibility issue between EclipseLink's H2 platform and the H2 version being used.\n\nKey findings:\n1. EclipseLink tried `DROP TABLE` + `CREATE TABLE` (it's doing drop-and-create despite our `create-tables` setting)\n2. The `CREATE TABLE` for accountejb, holdingejb, orderejb all fail because `INTEGER IDENTITY` is invalid H2 2.x syntax\n3. The quoteejb table succeeds because it doesn't have auto-increment columns\n4. Our manual `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS` from DatabasePopulator ran successfully first, but then EclipseLink's DDL dropped those tables and failed to recreate them\n\nThe fix is two-fold:\n1. Disable EclipseLink DDL generation completely (set to `none`)\n2. Let our DatabasePopulator handle ALL table creation with correct H2 2.x syntax\n\nLet me also check if our DatabasePopulator's `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS` ran at all or if EclipseLink ran first."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6213,"cache_read_input_tokens":29638,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6213,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":407},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"4c545541-8515-4b1c-a842-5c57d6a48e46"}
