{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01519bQjyrXAKPsPXEg2UVVw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `Creating database tables via JPA native queries` message is missing, which means EclipseLink's DDL ran first and raced with our startup bean. EclipseLink's `deploy-on-startup` triggered before our `@PostConstruct`, and EclipseLink dropped/recreated tables (but failed on 3 of them). Then our DatabasePopulator saw quoteejb existed (from EclipseLink's successful create), skipped createTables, and went straight to populate.\n\nWait - actually looking more carefully, the logs show EclipseLink doing `DROP TABLE quoteejb` which means it's doing `drop-and-create` even though we set `create-tables`. Let me re-examine the persistence.xml and fix this properly."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":641,"cache_read_input_tokens":35851,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":641,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":524},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"f9099906-529d-4297-900e-7ca1e2a95fce"}
