{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01MbVLopXSKDTCLPtS4Nnfyw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The container exited. Let me check the earlier logs I captured - they showed:\n- EclipseLink DDL tried to create tables with `INTEGER IDENTITY` (H2 1.x syntax) and failed for accountejb, holdingejb, orderejb\n- quoteejb and accountprofileejb were created successfully by EclipseLink (no auto-increment columns)\n- The log showed `TradeBuildDB: Populating DayTrader Database on startup...` and `TradeBuildDB: Creating 100 Quotes...` - so our DatabasePopulator DID run\n- But it never logged `Creating database tables via JPA native queries...`\n\nWait, let me re-examine: I see in the logs `TradeBuildDB: Creating 100 Quotes...` and `TradeBuildDB: Registering 50 Users...` but I don't see the `Creating database tables` message. This means either:\n1. `createTables()` ran but the log message was suppressed, OR\n2. The `createTables()` threw an exception silently\n\nLooking at the flow: `onStart()` calls `createTables()` first. In `createTables()`, `em.createNativeQuery(\"CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS quoteejb ...\")` would succeed (table exists), `accountprofileejb` would succeed (exists), but then `accountejb` with `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS` should also succeed because EclipseLink failed to create it.\n\nActually wait - looking at the log output I captured earlier more carefully, I see the EclipseLink DDL errors happened during persistence unit deployment (before our Singleton starts). Then I see our Singleton logs showing it went straight to populating. The missing `Creating database tables` log is suspicious.\n\nLet me look at the Log utility to understand:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":362,"cache_read_input_tokens":43869,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":362,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":604},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"59414428-2319-4504-914d-57701c6442b4"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01MbVLopXSKDTCLPtS4Nnfyw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_015M4JES2Ni4GEe82gorPu85","name":"Grep","input":{"pattern":"public static void log\\(","path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/util/Log.java","output_mode":"content","-A":5}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":362,"cache_read_input_tokens":43869,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":362,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":604},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"7169815d-946b-4323-8381-733379f02624"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015M4JES2Ni4GEe82gorPu85","type":"tool_result","content":"32:    public static void log(String message) {\n33-        log.log(Level.INFO, message);\n34-    }\n35-\n36:    public static void log(String msg1, String msg2) {\n37-        log(msg1 + msg2);\n38-    }\n39-\n40:    public static void log(String msg1, String msg2, String msg3) {\n41-        log(msg1 + msg2 + msg3);\n42-    }\n43-\n44-    public static void error(String message) {\n45-        message = \"Error: \" + message;"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"04eb50bb-2e0b-4f1e-a3ca-5f1790e55a07"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Vc4zCbNfhHiP2g4ug6QG8c","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The logs use `java.util.logging.Level.INFO`. Looking at the earlier captured output again, I can see the lines like `[INFO    ] TradeBuildDB: Creating 100 Quotes...` - so our logs DO appear. The `createTables` log is missing because something happened.\n\nI think the real issue is: our DatabasePopulator's `@PostConstruct` ran, called `createTables()`, but the `em.createNativeQuery` for `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS quoteejb` may have conflicted with EclipseLink's tables. Actually, wait - looking more closely at the issue: EclipseLink's DDL generation with `create-tables` is using `DROP TABLE` first? That's `drop-and-create-tables` behavior, not `create-tables`. There might be a bug where EclipseLink ignores the setting.\n\nRegardless, my fix (setting DDL to `none`) should solve this. With DDL disabled, EclipseLink won't try to drop or create any tables. Our DatabasePopulator's `createTables()` will handle everything. Let me rebuild and test.\n\nBut first, I also need to check: there may be a case-sensitivity issue with H2. H2 by default uppercases identifiers. Our tables are created as lowercase in SQL strings, but EclipseLink might query them as uppercase. Let me also check what the entity `@Column` annotations look like:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":761,"cache_read_input_tokens":44231,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":761,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":529},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"a9748de8-d31b-4d6a-864f-3619fa297a10"}
