→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"769eb108-4aff-4f00-a6b4-6a467c588d00"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01M5KJAq9gaTrXQkgRr4dKV9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good. The entity uses `@Column(name = \"ACCOUNTID\")` with uppercase names. H2 by default uppercases identifiers. Our `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS` uses uppercase column names. This should be fine.\n\nThe key issue was that EclipseLink's `create-tables` DDL was running with `INTEGER IDENTITY` syntax (incompatible with H2 2.x), causing tables with auto-increment PKs to fail. Setting DDL to `none` will prevent EclipseLink from trying to create/drop tables, and our DatabasePopulator will handle it.\n\nNow let me rebuild and test:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3237,"cache_read_input_tokens":46270,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3237,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":450},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"077f4427-d708-4aaf-ade3-030fcf384699"}
