{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01SB4mTYd16non6Xf5MSYSxL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Progress! Tables were created (no DDL errors from EclipseLink), and the quotes populated. But now the issue is `CALL IDENTITY()` - EclipseLink's H2Platform uses the old H2 1.x function `IDENTITY()` to retrieve generated IDs after insert. H2 2.x doesn't have this function.\n\nThis is the core EclipseLink/H2 2.x compatibility issue. The `H2Platform` class in EclipseLink is written for H2 1.x. I need to check the full log to see if tables were created:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2239,"cache_read_input_tokens":50912,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2239,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":245},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"3224a15e-7ad8-4080-bb2f-e5aaf548a4c0"}
