{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/, search for the implementation of:\n1. The login method that authenticates a user by userID and password\n2. The getAccountData method that retrieves an account by userID\n3. The register method\n\nLook in the jaxrs/TradeResource.java for the REST endpoints, and then trace into the service implementations (likely in impl/ejb3/TradeSLSBBean.java or impl/direct/TradeDirect.java).\n\nFocus on how account is looked up by userID - specifically any JPQL/SQL queries that join or look up accountejb by PROFILE_USERID. Return the relevant code snippets. This is read-only research."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014AwizJK1kGtU6rbwDRdo38","session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"9e57962f-5d52-4d53-bf44-b0595066f284"}
