{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01WYA6gsfLU8ZJ5sZ89TUeva","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_017LyRHEUsWXRZKfTonfjzz6","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"docker exec my_test_container_1 bash -c \"java -cp /config/lib/h2-2.2.224.jar org.h2.tools.Shell -url 'jdbc:h2:mem:tradedb;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1;MODE=LEGACY' -user sa -password '' -sql 'SELECT ACCOUNTID, PROFILE_USERID, BALANCE FROM accountejb WHERE PROFILE_USERID = '\\\"'\\\"'uid:0'\\\"'\\\"'' 2>&1\" 2>&1","description":"Query account data directly"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":559,"cache_read_input_tokens":75526,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":559,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":223},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"09df1edc-80e5-42d7-9b72-f5705c8cc65e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017LyRHEUsWXRZKfTonfjzz6","type":"tool_result","content":"Error: org.h2.jdbc.JdbcSQLSyntaxErrorException: Table \"ACCOUNTEJB\" not found (this database is empty); SQL statement:\nSELECT ACCOUNTID, PROFILE_USERID, BALANCE FROM accountejb WHERE PROFILE_USERID = 'uid:0' [42104-224]","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"6ab838f5-6241-4f93-9b73-3df6de70c22e"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_012jkjf8B523qfRT9FTJT9C9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The H2 Shell is creating a new connection to `mem:tradedb` but sees it as empty. This is because H2 in-memory databases are scoped to the JVM, and the Shell runs in a separate process. That approach won't work for inspecting data.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The `@OneToOne(mappedBy = \"profile\")` relationship on the inverse side (`AccountProfileDataBean.account`) requires EclipseLink to issue a SELECT on `accountejb` WHERE `PROFILE_USERID = ?`. If profile lookup works but `profile.getAccount()` returns null, then either:\n\n1. The SQL query runs but returns no results (data issue)\n2. EclipseLink can't resolve the relationship at all\n\nGiven that we created the table manually and populated via JPA, the data should be there. Let me check if there's an issue with how we set up the relationship during population. Looking at DatabasePopulator:\n\n```java\naccount.setProfile(profile);\nem.persist(account);\n```\n\nWe set the owning side (account -> profile), so the FK `PROFILE_USERID` should be set. But we DON'T set `profile.setAccount(account)`. This shouldn't matter for persistence (owning side handles FK), but for the current transaction's in-memory state, the profile object wouldn't have the account reference.\n\nHowever, when we load fresh from DB in a different request, EclipseLink should lazily resolve `profile.getAccount()`. Unless there's a problem with EclipseLink's weaving/lazy loading on Liberty.\n\nLet me check if the issue is with lazy loading of the inverse `@OneToOne`:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":310,"cache_read_input_tokens":76085,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":310,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":497},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"ce5ad074-509c-44c9-bfa5-69ef37c25c39"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_012jkjf8B523qfRT9FTJT9C9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_012kENaZ8yL3xXPF6WbLEeqA","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"docker logs my_test_container_1 2>&1 | grep -i \"weav\\|enhance\\|eclipselink.*agent\\|lazy\\|proxy\"","description":"Check EclipseLink weaving status"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":310,"cache_read_input_tokens":76085,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":310,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":497},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"3a52460a-baf1-48ae-9779-98b0684b7d6e"}
