{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01SxFGw8AVtzLPMmxcy9UgU3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I see Weld proxies but no EclipseLink weaving info. The key issue with `@OneToOne(mappedBy=...)` with `FetchType.LAZY` on the inverse side is a well-known JPA problem: EclipseLink requires weaving to make the inverse OneToOne actually lazy. Without proper weaving, EclipseLink might not resolve it at all.\n\nActually, the real issue might be simpler. Let me check: EclipseLink on Liberty usually does static weaving or dynamic weaving via the javaagent. But since we disabled DDL generation and the persistence unit might not be fully initializing the metadata for our manually-created tables...\n\nActually wait - let me reconsider. The `profile.getAccount()` just returns null. It's not throwing an exception. With `@OneToOne(mappedBy = \"profile\", fetch = FetchType.LAZY)`, if EclipseLink doesn't weave the entity, it may return null instead of a proxy. The fix is to either:\n\n1. Change the fetch to `EAGER` on the inverse side\n2. Change the `getAccountData` method to use a JPQL query instead of navigating the relationship\n\nOption 2 is better since it's less invasive. But actually, the simplest fix is to modify the `getAccountData` and `login` methods to query for the account directly. But these are in TradeSLSBBean which is not something we want to change extensively.\n\nLet me try the simplest fix: change `FetchType.LAZY` to `FetchType.EAGER` on the `AccountProfileDataBean.account` field:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1985,"cache_read_input_tokens":76395,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1985,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":773},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"07e5a62b-21b1-4bf4-ae39-5c592834c23e"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01SxFGw8AVtzLPMmxcy9UgU3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_012xrvk5TBSvRWhhGNJqQaFa","name":"TodoWrite","input":{"todos":[{"content":"Fix H2 DataSource configuration in server.xml","status":"completed","activeForm":"Fixing H2 DataSource configuration"},{"content":"Fix persistence.xml for EclipseLink (not Hibernate)","status":"completed","activeForm":"Fixing persistence.xml for EclipseLink"},{"content":"Add basic user registry to server.xml","status":"completed","activeForm":"Adding user registry to server.xml"},{"content":"Disable EclipseLink DDL generation - let DatabasePopulator create tables","status":"completed","activeForm":"Disabling EclipseLink DDL, fixing table creation"},{"content":"Fix H2 2.x IDENTITY() compatibility with LEGACY mode","status":"completed","activeForm":"Fixing H2 2.x IDENTITY() compatibility"},{"content":"Fix OneToOne inverse lazy loading for profile->account","status":"in_progress","activeForm":"Fixing OneToOne inverse lazy loading"},{"content":"Fix register endpoint serialization issue","status":"pending","activeForm":"Fixing register endpoint serialization"},{"content":"Rebuild, retest, and run smoke tests","status":"pending","activeForm":"Rebuilding and retesting"},{"content":"Document everything in CHANGELOG.md","status":"pending","activeForm":"Documenting in CHANGELOG.md"}]}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1985,"cache_read_input_tokens":76395,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1985,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":773},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc4c4d58-9b0e-47fb-9764-ecee6ff08c39","uuid":"515533cd-0605-4f9b-a609-4aea63c221e5"}
